(105, 2, '2013-11-18 22:38:00', '2013-11-18 22:38:00', 'A<b> Timpanometria </b>Ã© um exame utilizado para testar as condiÃ§Ãµes da orelha mÃ©dia e a mobilidade da membrana timpÃ¢nica e dos ossÃ­culos, atravÃ©s da variaÃ§Ã£o de pressÃ£o de ar no canal auditivo.\r\n\r\nTympanometry is an objective test of middle-ear function. It is not aÂ <a title="Hearing test" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hearing_test">hearing test</a>, but rather a measure of energy transmission through the middle ear. The test should not be used to assess the sensitivity of hearing and the results of this test should always be viewed in conjunction with pure tone<strong>Â <a title="Audiometry" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Audiometry">audiometry</a>.</strong>\r\n\r\nTympanometry is a valuable component of the audiometric evaluation. In evaluating hearing loss, tympanometry permits a distinction between sensorineural and conductive hearing loss, when evaluation is not apparent viaÂ <a title="Weber test" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weber_test">Weber</a>Â andÂ <a title="Rinne test" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rinne_test">Rinne</a>testing. Furthermore, in a primary care setting, tympanometry can be helpful in making the diagnosis of otitis media by demonstrating the presence of a middle ear effusion\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Timpanometria', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '102-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-18 22:38:00', '2013-11-18 22:38:00', '', 102, 'http://borgesdecarvalhootorrinos.com.br/sem-categoria/102-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(104, 2, '2013-11-18 22:20:45', '2013-11-18 22:20:45', 'A<b> Timpanometria</b>Â is an examination used to test the condition of theÂ <a title="Middle ear" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle_ear">middle ear</a><sup id="cite_ref-SteeleSusman2003_1-0"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tympanometry#cite_note-SteeleSusman2003-1">[1]</a></sup>Â and mobility of theÂ <a title="Eardrum" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eardrum">eardrum</a>Â (<a title="Tympanic membrane" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tympanic_membrane">tympanic membrane</a>) and the conduction bones by creating variations ofÂ <a title="Air pressure" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_pressure">air pressure</a>Â in the ear canal.\r\n\r\nTympanometry is an objective test of middle-ear function. It is not aÂ <a title="Hearing test" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hearing_test">hearing test</a>, but rather a measure of energy transmission through the middle ear. The test should not be used to assess the sensitivity of hearing and the results of this test should always be viewed in conjunction with pure tone<strong>Â <a title="Audiometry" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Audiometry">audiometry</a>.</strong>\r\n\r\nTympanometry is a valuable component of the audiometric evaluation. In evaluating hearing loss, tympanometry permits a distinction between sensorineural and conductive hearing loss, when evaluation is not apparent viaÂ <a title="Weber test" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weber_test">Weber</a>Â andÂ <a title="Rinne test" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rinne_test">Rinne</a>testing. Furthermore, in a primary care setting, tympanometry can be helpful in making the diagnosis of otitis media by demonstrating the presence of a middle ear effusion\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Timpanometria', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '102-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-18 22:20:45', '2013-11-18 22:20:45', '', 102, 'http://borgesdecarvalhootorrinos.com.br/sem-categoria/102-revision-v1/', 0, 'revisi